		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Here's a really crappy photo of my CRT TV (2C07 PPU). From what I can tell, it looks like colors match up so that evenHue = oddHue+2 (with wrap around, of course). E.g. the even scanline of $15 is the same hue as odd scanline of $13. (Looking at the TV the colors match up better than in the photo.)<br /><br />Which is funny, because in HardWareMan's cap it's quite clearly evenHue = oddHue+1.

		
