		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: PAL chroma merging?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Well, I took out my old monitor, which is used in the 90's. Do not look at the geometric distortion - I'll fix them later. The main feature of this monitor is that it is PAL decoder built on a good old TDA3510. This &quot;warm tube&quot; analog PAL decoder that utilizes the 64mks delay line. Therefore, the result really depends on the content of neighboring scanlines. In the new digital decoders, each scanline can be processed separately, although Avermedia shows almost identical to TDA3510 results.<br /><strong>UMC UA6538:</strong><br /><a href="http://savepic.ru/5823602.jpg" class="postlink"><img src="http://savepic.ru/5823602m.jpg" alt="Image" /></a><br /><strong>HA6538:</strong><br /><a href="http://savepic.ru/5783665.jpg" class="postlink"><img src="http://savepic.ru/5783665m.jpg" alt="Image" /></a><br /><a href="http://savepic.ru/5789809.jpg" class="postlink"><img src="http://savepic.ru/5789809m.jpg" alt="Image" /></a>

		

		</td>
	</tr>
